  "prompt": "What is citizen journalism?",
  "response": "Citizen journalism is a form of news reporting and content creation done by ordinary people who are not professional journalists. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Characteristics:\n- Individuals use digital technologies like smartphones, social media, and blogs\n- Report on events and news happening in their local communities\n- Share firsthand accounts and perspectives\n- Often provide real-time coverage of breaking news\n- Typically unpaid and not affiliated with traditional media organizations\n\n2. Benefits:\n- Provides alternative perspectives\n- Can cover events traditional media might miss\n- Enables broader and more diverse news coverage\n- Allows immediate reporting from the scene of events\n- Increases public participation in news gathering\n\n3. Platforms:\n- Social media networks\n- Blogs\n- YouTube\n- Independent news websites\n- Crowdsourced reporting platforms\n\n4. Limitations:\n- Potential lack of professional journalistic standards\n- Risk of misinformation or bias\n- Less rigorous fact-checking\n- Varying levels of credibility\n\n5. Examples:\n- Eyewitness videos of protests\n- Live social media updates during emergencies\n- Citizen-reported coverage of local community events\n\nCitizen journalism represents a democratization of news reporting, enabling individuals to contribute to public discourse and information sharing.",
